description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting new role for a pharmacist to join our expanding team. Promising you a variety of experiences across both primary and secondary care, this new joint post will draw on the skills you have acquired in community pharmacy, primary-care or secondary-care and will involve the majority of your time working with a small friendly team across four GP practices within Woolston and Townhill PCN. Here you will work within the practice clinical teams and with pharmacy technicians to provide medicines support to patients and also to those patients within care homes in the area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For some of your time you will also work with the Medicines Management Team covering Solent NHS Trust services based in Southampton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These patient focussed roles will see you become an integrated member of the healthcare team working with a variety of different multidisciplinary team members to achieve both PCN and Hospital based outcomes. You will receive coaching and training within the PCN to enable you to work effectively both under the supervision of other team members and autonomously, managing your own time and workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is offered as full time (up to 37 ½ hours per work) or part time with the flexibility to fit your hours around the needs of the services whilst being able to achieve work – life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that should this post attract sufficient interest, we may choose to close at an earlier date. We strongly suggest that you apply at an early stage. &lt;strong&gt;If we have not contacted you within four weeks of the closing date of this post, please presume that you have not been selected.&lt;/strong&gt; Candidates selected for interview will be contacted within 2-3 weeks; therefore you should check your emails regularly including junk mail folders.&lt;/p&gt;
